Subject: [PATCH 0010] DEBUG: instrument exec + binfmt_elf + mmap — round 5

Round 4 showed: vm_mmap(addr=0, len=0x70000, prot=5, type=MAP_PRIVATE,
off=0) returns -EINVAL for the interpreter.  The main binary loads fine
with MAP_FIXED_NOREPLACE at region 4/6.

Round 5 instruments __get_unmapped_area() to show exactly which check
returns -EINVAL: arch_mmap_check, get_area callback, mm_get_unmapped_area,
addr>TASK_SIZE, offset_in_page, or security_mmap_addr.

Also instruments do_mmap to distinguish __get_unmapped_area vs
mmap_region failures.

